The bug was fixed, I called people into work, and I had the servers shut down for an emergency update.

This does not happen often, but when it does, we must act quickly.

If something similar were to happen again in the future I would bring them down again.

To those of you whose evenings were disrupted, I apologize. We will endeavor to minimize these occurances.

To the Verant employees who had to direct this operation and/or come into work, I am also sorry.

No one likes downtime, not us, not the players. 

That said, to the complainers and flamers in this thread: think for a moment, and think about the game as a whole. Some of you act like kids who are mad at their parents for not letting them play in the street. My god, do you think we bring down servers like this for giggles? 

To everyone else, again, sorry for the disruption.

-Brad
